Task 1: Environment Setup and Configuration
Step 1: Install Required Tools
Update your system and install patch management dependencies:

# Update package lists
sudo apt update

# Install required packages
sudo apt install -y python3-pip python3-venv unattended-upgrades apt-listchanges

# Install Python packages
pip3 install pyyaml schedule psutil requests

# Install security scanning tools
sudo apt install -y lynis
Step 2: Create Project Structure
Set up an organized directory structure:

# Create project directory
mkdir -p ~/patch-management-lab
cd ~/patch-management-lab

# Create subdirectories
mkdir -p {scripts,configs,logs,reports}

# Create initial files
touch scripts/__init__.py
touch configs/patch_config.yaml
Step 3: Configure Automated Updates
Configure the unattended-upgrades package:

# Enable unattended upgrades
sudo dpkg-reconfigure -plow unattended-upgrades

# Create custom configuration
sudo tee /etc/apt/apt.conf.d/20auto-upgrades << 'EOF'
APT::Periodic::Update-Package-Lists "1";
APT::Periodic::Download-Upgradeable-Packages "1";
APT::Periodic::AutocleanInterval "7";
APT::Periodic::Unattended-Upgrade "1";
EOF
Step 4: Create Configuration File
Create a YAML configuration file for patch management settings:

# configs/patch_config.yaml
patch_settings:
  auto_reboot: false
  maintenance_window: "02:00-04:00"
  excluded_packages: []
  security_only: true

notification:
  email_enabled: false
  webhook_url: null

logging:
  level: INFO
  file: logs/patch_activity.log
